        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer57121087" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7225668984144448583">This book is rather poetic. Augusten Burroughs has not had the healthiest family and childhood in the world. It&apos;s interesting to read about people&apos;s less than ideal childhoods. It has the effect of making me feel a bit hopeful. As if people can somehow be successful and eventually whole despite all of that.<br/><br/>But man, Augusten&apos;s father frustrated me. Books about dysfunctional childhoods are also very depression and stressful. Like all Augusten wanted was some affection but he didn&apos;t get it. But his</span>
  <span id="freeText7225668984144448583" style="display:none">This book is rather poetic. Augusten Burroughs has not had the healthiest family and childhood in the world. It's interesting to read about people's less than ideal childhoods. It has the effect of making me feel a bit hopeful. As if people can somehow be successful and eventually whole despite all of that.<br /><br />But man, Augusten's father frustrated me. Books about dysfunctional childhoods are also very depression and stressful. Like all Augusten wanted was some affection but he didn't get it. But his poor father ALSO had a messed up childhood. Going from being treasured to hit for asking for a bedtime story. The thing about dysfunction is it can be passed down from one generation to the next, but you can say, wait a minute, what I been through was screwed up and I won't let my children go through it. It will be difficult, but it can be done.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7225668984144448583" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


